      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "Early morning: In steep terrain there is a danger of falling on the hard snow surface. The surface of the snowpack has frozen to form a strong crust and will soften later than the day before. <br/> In particular very steep sunny slopes and base of rock walls: Medium-sized wet and gliding avalanches are to be expected below approximately 2300 m. <br/> <br/> Weak layers exist deeper in the snowpack. Single winter sport participants can release avalanches in some places. These can be triggered in deep layers and reach large size. These avalanche prone locations are barely recognisable, even to the trained eye. <br/> Remotely triggered avalanches are possible in isolated cases.",
        "highlights": "In particular very steep sunny slopes base of rock walls: The danger of moist and wet avalanches will increase a little during the day."
